API docs by Redocly

Dynizer API (2.2)

Download OpenAPI specification:

Consono: support@consono.ai URL: https://www.consono.ai

Public API for the Dynizer knowledge engine.
All endpoints are under /api/v2, secured with JWT unless stated otherwise.
See the Dynizer overview for architecture details.

List Users

List users with optional pagination window.
Defaults to returning all users.

Authorizations:
JWT
query Parameters
window.limit
required
integer <int64>

Defines how many records at max are returned.
If fewer records are available, all will be returned.
Setting this to -1 will be interpreted as no limit

window.offset
required
integer <int64>

Defines the offset at which to start reading.
An offset of 0 will bean to start from the first possible record.

window.relative
boolean

The Dynizer keeps track of the last read position, this flag indicates wether the offset is relative to the current read position or absolute.

Responses

https://*.dynizer.com/api/v2/users

Response samples

  • 200
  • 401
  • 500
  • default
Content type
application/json
{
  • "total_users": 0,
  • "users": [
    • {
      • "user_name": "string",
      • "roles": [
        • {
          • "name": "string"
          }
        ],
      • "enabled": true
      }
    ]
}

JWT

required

This is used to create an Action.

The if_not_exists flag allows if set not to raise an error if the Action already exists.

required
string

The unique name for the Action.
Use the CheckActionName, call to verify the name, without trying to create it.

List Action Names

Authorizations:
JWT
path Parameters
action_type_label
required
string

The name of the ActionType.

query Parameters
window.limit
required
integer <int64>

Defines how many records at max are returned.
If fewer records are available, all will be returned.
Setting this to -1 will be interpreted as no limit

window.offset
required
integer <int64>

Defines the offset at which to start reading.
An offset of 0 will bean to start from the first possible record.

window.relative
boolean

The Dynizer keeps track of the last read position, this flag indicates wether the offset is relative to the current read position or absolute.

order_field
string
Default: "Created"
Enum: "Created" "Name"

By which field to order Action names.

  • Created: order by created
  • Name: order by name
order_direction
string
Default: "Asc"
Enum: "Asc" "Desc"

Order in which to load the Action names.

  • Asc: order ascending
  • Desc: order descending

Delete Action

Delete an Action.
Fails if Instances exist unless cascade=true, which marks the action and its instances as deleted.

Authorizations:
JWT
path Parameters
action_name
required
string

The current name of the Action to be deleted.

query Parameters
cascade
boolean

This flag allows to mark all associated Instances as deleted.
If cascade == false an error is raised if this Action has Instances.
Action with no Instances can be deleted no matter what value cascade has.

Responses

Add ActionLabel

Add an ActionLabel to an existing Action.
Use CheckActionLabelName first to validate the name.

Authorizations:
JWT
path Parameters
action_name
required
string

The unique name for the Action.
Use the CheckActionName, call to verify the name, without trying to create it.

Request Body schema: application/json
required
if_not_exists
boolean

if set to true -> NO ERROR is returned if a Action already has an ActionLabel by the provided name.
No changes to the ActionLabel will be performed when if_not_exists == true and the ActionLabel already exists.

action_label_name
required
string

The unique name of the ActionLabel within the **Action.
Use the CheckActionLabelName, call to verify the name, without creating it.

component
required
string (ComponentType)
Default: "InvalidComponentType"
Enum: "InvalidComponentType" "Who" "What" "Where" "When"
  • Who: subject data category
  • What: object data category
  • Where: spatial data category
  • When: temporal data category
default_data_type
required
string (DataType)
Default: "InvalidDataType"

Create Object

Create an object reference used to store large values of type TEXT, CLOB, BLOB, or DOCUMENT.
TEXT is indexed by FullTextIndex if enabled; CLOB is an unindexed character LOB; BLOB is an unindexed binary LOB; DOCUMENT holds JSON document analysis output.

string

old value for the share

new_value
required
string

Value for the share

data_type
required
string (DataType)
Default: "InvalidDataType"
Enum: "InvalidDataType" "DT_Integer" "DT_String" "DT_Boolean" "DT_Decimal" "DT_Timestamp" "DT_Uri" "DT_Void" "DT_Float" "DT_UnsignedInteger" "DT_Binary" "DT_Uuid" "DT_Text" "DT_Blob" "DT_Clob" "DT_Document" "DT_Any" "DT_Delete"
  • DT_Integer: Integer
  • DT_String: String
  • DT_Boolean: Boolean
  • DT_Decimal: Decimal fixed
  • DT_Timestamp: Timestamp
  • DT_Uri: URI
  • DT_Void: VOID is a designated DataType to indicate no value
  • DT_Float: Float
  • DT_UnsignedInteger: UInt
  • DT_Binary: Byte Array
  • DT_Uuid: UUID
  • DT_Text: FullTextIndex large object
  • DT_Blob: Binary large object
  • DT_Clob: Character large object
  • DT_Document: Document large object, stores/indexes document analysis output
  • DT_Any: DT_Date = 16; DT_Time = 17; special flag to indicate all DataTypes, to be used in AlternativeDataTypes for ActionLabels and MetaDataKeys
  • DT_Delete: special flag to indicate that the value is to be removed

Responses
